Vendoring policy (InGENeer):
- Clean mirror of the upstream library headers (CDT/include/) at the commit recorded in
  UPSTREAM_COMMIT. Upstream docs/, visualizer/, tests, and build scaffolding are omitted.
- NO local modifications. Do not fork; do not patch in place. To change behavior, wrap it
  in libs/geometry_core. To update, re-vendor a newer upstream commit and update
  UPSTREAM_COMMIT.
- MPL-2.0 is file-level copyleft: if a vendored file is ever modified (avoid this), that
  file's source must remain available under MPL-2.0. This is compatible with the
  Apache-2.0 open Core (ADR-0021) when consumed unmodified, as here.
